{"id":992036496,"question_id":2,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"11 months, 2 weeks","timestamp":1689097378,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"2 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/992036496/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Add Two Numbers","memory":"43.1 MB","code":"/**\n * Definition for singly-linked list.\n * public class ListNode {\n *     int val;\n *     ListNode next;\n *     ListNode() {}\n *     ListNode(int val) { this.val = val; }\n *     ListNode(int val, ListNode next) { this.val = val; this.next = next; }\n * }\n */\nclass Solution {\n    public ListNode addTwoNumbers(ListNode l1, ListNode l2) {\n        ListNode res = new ListNode();\n        ListNode cur = res;\n        int carry=0, sum=0;\n        while(l1!=null || l2!=null|| carry!=0){\n            sum = 0;\n            sum+=(l1!=null)?l1.val:0;\n            l1 = (l1!=null)?l1.next:null;\n\n            sum+=(l2!=null)?l2.val:0;\n            l2 = (l2!=null)?l2.next:null;\n\n            sum+=carry;\n            cur.next = new ListNode(sum%10);\n            carry = sum/10;\n            cur = cur.next;\n        }\n\n        return res.next;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"add-two-numbers","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
